A wax figure of American rapper Nicki Minaj was unveiled at Madame Tussauds in Berlin. JOHANNESBURG - A new wax figure of American rapper Nicki Minaj unveiled at Madame Tussauds in Berlin on Tuesday has left many fans confused. READ: Rapper Nicki Minaj announces retirement The figure was inspired by a scene from the rapper's 2014 "Anaconda" music video. Despite the accurate recreation of her outfit and the jungle-like setting from the video, several fans took to social media and said that Minaj’s facial features are not an accurate representation of the rapper.